<div class='questionText'>
<a href="/questions/886683-i-was-interested-in-reading-this-book-but">I was interested in reading this book, but after reading a few comments I have second thoughts. is this another book that uses confirmation bias to &quot;prove&quot; its point? I stay away from books that have nice stories that fit what the author is trying to prove, so before I waste my time can someone please give me more info: is it possible that there are a lot of people who did &quot;deep work&quot; and failed?</a>
</div>
