<div id="review_1535394682" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1535394682" />
    <a title="Mario Tomic" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/18944510-mario-tomic"><img alt="Mario Tomic" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1528799694p2/18944510.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1535394682?book_show_action=true">Oct 20, 2016</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Mario Tomic" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Mario Tomic" href="/user/show/18944510-mario-tomic">Mario Tomic</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1535394682" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1260283757582293689">Deep work is probably my favorite book I&apos;ve read this year, and I can&apos;t recommend it enough. In the age of knowledge work, with so many things going on, the ability to do focus and do deep work is a precious asset to have. As Cal says: &quot;Focus is the new IQ.&quot; We can all agree that there&apos;s just too many distractions happening around us, smartphones, apps, social media and all the things we&apos;re enjoying today have turned us into multi-tasking machines. Unfortunately for us, our brains aren&apos;t designe</span>
  <span id="freeText1260283757582293689" style="display:none">Deep work is probably my favorite book I've read this year, and I can't recommend it enough. In the age of knowledge work, with so many things going on, the ability to do focus and do deep work is a precious asset to have. As Cal says: "Focus is the new IQ." We can all agree that there's just too many distractions happening around us, smartphones, apps, social media and all the things we're enjoying today have turned us into multi-tasking machines. Unfortunately for us, our brains aren't designed for multitasking while simultaneously being able to produce very deep meaningful work. As I said above, this is a very valuable book for the age we live in. Highly recommended!</span>
  <a data-text-id="1260283757582293689" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

